On Thu, 19 Jul 2007, Greg Potts wrote:

> Hi Glenn,
>
> A very quick number-crunching tells me that one motor per rear wheel
> gets you 20HP total power available.

Electric horsepower is rated very differently than gasoline horsepower.

Since electric motors deliver full torque from zero RPM and have a
relatively flat torque/rpm curve, you don't need as high a horesepower
rating as you do with gasoline.
